'''Barí''' is a [[Chibchan]] language spoken in Northwestern [[South America]] by the [[Motilone Barí|Barí]] ([[Motilon people|Motilon]]). The Motilon are sometimes called "dobocubi", but this is a pejorative term.<ref name="e18"/>
