'''Camera coverage''', in [[filmmaking]] and [[video production]], is the amount of [[footage]] shot and different [[camera angle]]s used to capture a scene.  When in the [[post-production]] process, the more camera coverage means that there is more footage for the [[film editor]] to work with in assembling the [[Final cut (film editing)|final cut]].

