A '''segment''' of handwriting is a piece of the pen-tip [[trajectory]] between two defined segmentation points. If the occurrence of a minimum in the absolute (tangential) [[velocity]] is used as a heuristic for segmentation, the pen-tip [[trajectory]] can be subdivided into segments corresponding to [[ballistic stroke]]s.

In [[handwriting recognition]] or [[optical character recognition]], other terminologies may be used, such as the term [[glyph]] for a non-character (i.e.: sub character or 
multi-character) pattern.

